The paper deals with machine learning and robotics, specifically in the area of imitation learning. The paper proposes a new approach to active imitation learning, which is a subfield of machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper also discusses the use of an environment simulator, which is commonly used in robotics and control systems (cs.RO and cs.SY). Additionally, the paper evaluates the proposed algorithm on four test domains, which suggests a focus on computer vision (cs.CV). Overall, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG and cs.AI, as the paper deals with machine learning and artificial intelligence techniques.
